    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Looking for a budget-friendly set of wheels with plenty of life left in it? This car isn\u2019t perfect, but it starts, runs, and offers a great opportunity for someone who wants inexpensive transportation or a solid little project. A straightforward, honest car at a price that makes sense\u2014ideal for a first car, backup vehicle, or anyone handy who enjoys getting the most out of a good deal. If you want something affordable without spending a fortune, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 5495.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 31
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Solid budget-friendly project or utility driver with strong fixer-upper potential. This car shows its age cosmetically and will need attention, but it still offers a dependable mechanical foundation and a straightforward platform for someone who knows their way around basic maintenance. The powertrain pulls through the rev range, the chassis feels usable, and it\u2019s a great candidate for a work commuter, parts donor, or restoration-minded buyer looking for an affordable entry point. If you want inexpensive transportation with upside for the right owner, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 5900.0,
